bia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Rhydderch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh:  see  Roderick  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Roderick","meanings":["Welsh (Glamorgan): Anglicized form of the Welsh personal name <i>Rhydderch</i> (British Celtic <i>Rodercos</i>, presumably meaning ‘great seer’ or ‘most high’), the name of a prominent figure in first-millennium Welsh history. Compare   Prothero  ."]}]},{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewelyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llywelyn ap Rhydderch was born in 1384, in Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Rhydderch ap Owain, was 26 and his mother, Mrs. Rhydderch ap Owain, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Joan ferch Philip. He died in Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1384–":"1384–Surnud","1384–Male":"1384–Surnud","1388–Female":"1388–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1358–Male":"1358–Surnud","1359–Female":"1359–Surnud","1359":"1359","1358":"1358","1388":"1388","1384":"1384","of Is Cennen,Cantref Mawr,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1384–":"1384–Kuollut","1384–Male":"1384–Kuollut","1388–Female":"1388–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1358–Male":"1358–Kuollut","1359–Female":"1359–Kuollut","1359":"1359","1358":"1358","1388":"1388","1384":"1384","of Is Cennen,Cantref Mawr,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1384–":"1384–Décédé","1384–Male":"1384–Décédé","1388–Female":"1388–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1358–Male":"1358–Décédé","1359–Female":"1359–Décédée","1359":"1359","1358":"1358","1388":"1388","1384":"1384","of Is Cennen,Cantref Mawr,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Llywelyn ap Rhydderch est né en 1384, à Carmarthenshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, Rhydderch ap Owain, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Mrs. Rhydderch ap Owain, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan ferch Philip. Il est décédé à Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1384–